<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title><%= pageTitle %></title>
  <meta name="description" content="<%= metaDescription %>">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://mytaxcalcs.com/<%= state.slug %>-income-tax-calculator">
  <meta property="og:title" content="<%= ogTitle %>">
  <meta property="og:description" content="<%= ogDescription %>">
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://mytaxcalcs.com/<%= state.slug %>-income-tax-calculator">
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">
  <meta property="og:site_name" content="MyTaxCalcs">
  <meta property="og:image" content="https://mytaxcalcs.com/images/og-default.png">
  <meta property="og:image:width" content="1200">
  <meta property="og:image:height" content="630">
  <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
  <meta name="twitter:title" content="<%= ogTitle %>">
  <meta name="twitter:description" content="<%= ogDescription %>">
  <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://mytaxcalcs.com/images/og-default.png">
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" sizes="any">
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml">
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/favicon.png">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-FS9HCDT0D7"></script>
  <script>window.dataLayer=window.dataLayer||[];function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}gtag('js',new Date());gtag('config','G-FS9HCDT0D7');</script>
  <script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5193834725888549" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <style>
    /* State page additions */
    .calc-page{max-width:780px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px 60px}
    .calc-page-header{padding:28px 0 24px}
    .calc-page-header h1{font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin:0 0 10px;color:#111827}
    .calc-page-header p{font-size:1rem;color:#6b7280;margin:0;max-width:580px}
    .state-overview-section{background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem 1.75rem;margin:2rem 0}
    .state-overview-section h2{font-size:1.15rem;color:#111827;margin:0 0 .75rem;font-weight:700}
    .state-overview-section p{color:#374151;line-height:1.7;margin:0;font-size:.95rem}
    .key-facts-bar{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1px;background:#e5e7eb;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;margin:2rem 0}
    .fact-item{flex:1 1 150px;background:#fff;padding:1rem 1.25rem;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:.25rem}
    .fact-label{font-size:.7rem;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.06em;color:#6b7280}
    .fact-value{font-size:.95rem;font-weight:700;color:#111827}
    .fact-value a{font-size:.82rem;font-weight:600;color:#16a34a;text-decoration:none}
    .fact-value a:hover{text-decoration:underline}
    .bracket-section{margin:2rem 0}
    .bracket-section h2{font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin:0 0 .4rem}
    .bracket-section>p{color:#4b5563;margin:0 0 1rem;font-size:.9rem}
    .bracket-table-wrap{overflow-x:auto;border-radius:10px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb}
    .bracket-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.9rem}
    .bracket-table thead{background:#16a34a;color:#fff}
    .bracket-table thead th{padding:.7rem 1rem;text-align:left;font-weight:600}
    .bracket-table tbody tr:nth-child(even){background:#f9fafb}
    .bracket-table tbody tr:hover{background:#f0fdf4}
    .bracket-table tbody td{padding:.6rem 1rem;color:#111827;border-bottom:1px solid #f3f4f6}
    .bracket-note{font-size:.78rem;color:#9ca3af;margin:.5rem 0 0}
    .bracket-note a{color:#16a34a}
    .flat-rate-callout{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1.25rem;background:#f0fdf4;border:2px solid #16a34a;border-radius:12px;padding:1.25rem 1.75rem;margin:1rem 0}
    .flat-rate-number{font-size:2.75rem;font-weight:800;color:#16a34a;line-height:1}
    .flat-rate-label{font-size:.95rem;color:#374151;font-weight:500}
    .no-tax-callout{display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:1rem;background:#f0fdf4;border:2px solid #16a34a;border-radius:12px;padding:1.25rem 1.75rem;margin:2rem 0}
    .no-tax-icon{font-size:1.75rem;color:#16a34a;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;flex-shrink:0}
    .no-tax-callout h2{font-size:1.1rem;color:#111827;margin:0 0 .35rem;font-weight:700}
    .no-tax-callout p{color:#374151;margin:0;font-size:.9rem}
    .worked-example-section{margin:2rem 0}
    .worked-example-section h2{font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin:0 0 .4rem}
    .worked-example-section>p{color:#4b5563;margin:0 0 1rem;font-size:.9rem}
    .example-box{border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden}
    .example-scenario{background:#f9fafb;padding:.7rem 1.25rem;font-size:.85rem;color:#374151;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb}
    .example-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.88rem}
    .example-table th{background:#f3f4f6;padding:.55rem 1.25rem;text-align:left;font-weight:600;color:#374151;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb}
    .example-table th:last-child,.example-table td:last-child{text-align:right}
    .example-table td{padding:.55rem 1.25rem;color:#111827;border-bottom:1px solid #f3f4f6}
    .example-table tfoot td{background:#f0fdf4;font-weight:700;color:#15803d;border-top:2px solid #bbf7d0;border-bottom:none}
    .state-faq-section{margin:2rem 0}
    .state-faq-section h2{font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin:0 0 1rem}
    .state-faq-item{border-bottom:1px solid #f3f4f6;padding:.9rem 0}
    .state-faq-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
    .state-faq-item h3{font-size:.92rem;font-weight:700;color:#111827;margin:0 0 .35rem}
    .state-faq-item p{color:#4b5563;margin:0;line-height:1.6;font-size:.88rem}
    .state-faq-item a{color:#16a34a}
    @media(max-width:600px){
      .key-facts-bar{flex-direction:column;gap:0}
      .fact-item{border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb}
      .flat-rate-callout{flex-direction:column;gap:.5rem}
      .no-tax-callout{flex-direction:column}
    }
  </style>
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebApplication",
    "name": "<%= pageTitle %>",
    "description": "<%= metaDescription %>",
    "url": "https://mytaxcalcs.com/<%= state.slug %>-income-tax-calculator",
    "applicationCategory": "FinanceApplication",
    "operatingSystem": "Web",
    "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
    "provider": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "MyTaxCalcs", "url": "https://mytaxcalcs.com" }
  }
  </script>
</head>
<body>

  <header class="site-header">
    <nav class="nav">
      <a href="/" class="logo">
        <span class="logo-mark">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <rect x="1" y="1" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e"/>
            <rect x="11" y="1" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.5"/>
            <rect x="1" y="11" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.5"/>
            <rect x="11" y="11" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.25"/>
          </svg>
        </span>
        <span>MyTaxCalcs</span>
      </a>
      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/calculators">Calculators</a>
        <a href="/states">States</a>
        <a href="/blog">Blog</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
      </div>
      <a class="nav-cta" href="/calculators">All Calculators</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <div class="page-with-sidebar">
  <main>
    <div class="calc-page">

      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb-sep">&#8250;</span>
        <a href="/states">States</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb-sep">&#8250;</span>
        <span><%= state.name %> Income Tax Calculator</span>
      </nav>

      <div class="calc-page-header">
        <div class="page-eyebrow">
          <%= state.abbr %> State Tax
        </div>
        <h1><%= state.name %> Income Tax Calculator</h1>
        <% if (state.hasIncomeTax) { %>
          <p>Estimate your 2025 <%= state.name %> state and federal income tax. Includes <%= state.name %> tax brackets, a worked dollar example, and filing tips.</p>
        <% } else { %>
          <p><%= state.name %> has no state income tax. Estimate your federal income tax as a <%= state.name %> resident for 2025.</p>
        <% } %>
      </div>

      <div class="ad-zone">
        <div class="ad-zone-label">Advertisement</div>
        <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-5193834725888549" data-ad-slot="4212978293" data-ad-format="auto" data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
        <script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
      </div>

      <!-- Key Facts Bar -->
      <div class="key-facts-bar">
        <div class="fact-item">
          <span class="fact-label">State Income Tax</span>
          <span class="fact-value"><%= state.hasIncomeTax ? state.brackets : 'None' %></span>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <span class="fact-label">Top Rate</span>
          <span class="fact-value"><%= state.hasIncomeTax ? state.topRate + '%' : '0%' %></span>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <span class="fact-label">Tax Type</span>
          <span class="fact-value">
            <% if (!state.hasIncomeTax) { %>No Income Tax<% } else if (state.topRate === state.bottomRate) { %>Flat Rate<% } else { %>Graduated<% } %>
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="fact-item">
          <span class="fact-label">Official Source</span>
          <span class="fact-value"><a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a></span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- State Overview -->
      <div class="state-overview-section">
        <h2><%= state.name %> State Income Tax Overview</h2>
        <p><%= state.overview %></p>
      </div>

      <!-- GRADUATED STATE: bracket table + worked example -->
      <% if (state.hasIncomeTax && state.bracketRows && state.bracketRows.length > 0) { %>
      <div class="bracket-section">
        <h2><%= state.name %> Income Tax Brackets (2025)</h2>
        <p>These are the <%= state.name %> state income tax brackets for single filers. Only the income within each bracket is taxed at that rate — not your entire income.</p>
        <div class="bracket-table-wrap">
          <table class="bracket-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Taxable Income</th><th>Tax Rate</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <% state.bracketRows.forEach(function(row) { %>
              <tr>
                <td><% if (row.max === null) { %>Over $<%= row.min.toLocaleString() %><% } else { %>$<%= row.min.toLocaleString() %> – $<%= row.max.toLocaleString() %><% } %></td>
                <td><%= row.rate %>%</td>
              </tr>
              <% }); %>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="bracket-note">Source: <a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a>. Brackets shown are for single filers. Married filing jointly thresholds may differ.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="worked-example-section">
        <h2>What a <%= state.name %> Resident Actually Pays: A Worked Example</h2>
        <p>Your effective tax rate is almost always lower than your top bracket. Here is how the math works for a single filer earning $65,000.</p>
        <div class="example-box">
          <div class="example-scenario"><strong>Scenario:</strong> Single filer, $65,000 in taxable income</div>
          <div id="worked-example-output"></div>
        </div>
        <script>
        (function() {
          var brackets = <%- JSON.stringify(state.bracketRows) %>;
          var income = 65000;
          var tax = 0;
          var rows = [];
          for (var i = 0; i < brackets.length; i++) {
            var b = brackets[i];
            if (income <= b.min) break;
            var upper = b.max === null ? income : Math.min(b.max, income);
            var chunk = upper - b.min;
            var amount = chunk * (b.rate / 100);
            tax += amount;
            rows.push({ rate: b.rate, chunk: chunk, amount: amount });
          }
          var effectiveRate = (tax / income * 100).toFixed(1);
          var fmt = function(n) { return '$' + n.toLocaleString('en-US', {minimumFractionDigits:2, maximumFractionDigits:2}); };
          var html = '<table class="example-table"><thead><tr><th>Bracket</th><th>Income in Bracket</th><th>Tax</th></tr></thead><tbody>';
          rows.forEach(function(r) {
            html += '<tr><td>' + r.rate + '%</td><td>' + fmt(r.chunk) + '</td><td>' + fmt(r.amount) + '</td></tr>';
          });
          html += '</tbody><tfoot>';
          html += '<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Total State Tax on $65,000</strong></td><td><strong>' + fmt(tax) + '</strong></td></tr>';
          html += '<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Effective State Tax Rate</strong></td><td><strong>' + effectiveRate + '%</strong></td></tr>';
          html += '</tfoot></table>';
          document.getElementById('worked-example-output').innerHTML = html;
        })();
        </script>
      </div>

      <!-- FLAT RATE STATE -->
      <% } else if (state.hasIncomeTax && state.topRate === state.bottomRate) { %>
      <div class="bracket-section">
        <h2><%= state.name %> Income Tax Rate (2025)</h2>
        <p><%= state.name %> uses a flat income tax rate — the same percentage applies to all taxable income regardless of how much you earn.</p>
        <div class="flat-rate-callout">
          <span class="flat-rate-number"><%= state.topRate %>%</span>
          <span class="flat-rate-label">Flat rate on all taxable income</span>
        </div>
        <p class="bracket-note">Source: <a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="worked-example-section">
        <h2>What a <%= state.name %> Resident Actually Pays: A Worked Example</h2>
        <div class="example-box">
          <div class="example-scenario"><strong>Scenario:</strong> Single filer, $65,000 in taxable income</div>
          <table class="example-table">
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Taxable Income</td><td>$65,000.00</td></tr>
              <tr><td><%= state.name %> Flat Rate</td><td><%= state.topRate %>%</td></tr>
            </tbody>
            <tfoot>
              <tr><td><strong>Estimated State Tax</strong></td><td><strong>$<%= (650 * state.topRate).toFixed(2) %></strong></td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Effective Rate</strong></td><td><strong><%= state.topRate %>%</strong></td></tr>
            </tfoot>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- NO-TAX STATE -->
      <% } else { %>
      <div class="no-tax-callout">
        <div class="no-tax-icon">✓</div>
        <div>
          <h2><%= state.name %> Has No State Income Tax</h2>
          <p><%= state.noTaxNote %></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p style="color:#4b5563;font-size:.9rem;margin:0 0 2rem">As a <%= state.name %> resident, your state income tax is $0. The calculator below estimates your <strong>federal</strong> income tax, which applies to all U.S. residents regardless of state.</p>
      <% } %>

      <!-- RESULTS (shown after POST) -->
      <% if (result) { %>
      <div class="result-card">
        <div class="result-card-header">
          <div class="result-icon">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M7 8h4M7 12h8"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h2>Your Tax Estimate</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="result-primary">
          <span class="result-label"><%= result.refundOrOwed >= 0 ? 'Estimated Refund' : 'Estimated Amount Owed' %></span>
          <span class="result-amount <%= result.refundOrOwed >= 0 ? '' : 'owed' %>">$<%= Math.abs(Math.round(result.refundOrOwed)).toLocaleString() %></span>
        </div>
        <div class="result-grid">
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Gross Income</div>
            <div class="ri-value">$<%= Math.round(result.grossIncome).toLocaleString() %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Deduction Used</div>
            <div class="ri-value">$<%= Math.round(result.deduction).toLocaleString() %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Taxable Income</div>
            <div class="ri-value">$<%= Math.round(result.taxableIncome).toLocaleString() %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Federal Tax After Credits</div>
            <div class="ri-value red">$<%= Math.round(result.federalTaxAfterCredits).toLocaleString() %></div>
          </div>
          <% if (state.hasIncomeTax && result.stateTax != null) { %>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label"><%= state.name %> State Tax (Est.)</div>
            <div class="ri-value red">$<%= Math.round(result.stateTax).toLocaleString() %></div>
          </div>
          <% } %>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Effective Tax Rate</div>
            <div class="ri-value"><%= (result.effectiveTaxRate * 100).toFixed(1) %>%</div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Marginal Tax Rate</div>
            <div class="ri-value"><%= (result.marginalRate * 100).toFixed(1) %>%</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <% } %>

      <!-- FORM -->
      <div class="calc-card-form">
        <h2>Enter Your Tax Information</h2>
        <form method="POST" action="/<%= state.slug %>-income-tax-calculator">
          <div class="form-grid">
            <div class="form-field full">
              <label for="grossIncome">Gross Annual Income</label>
              <div class="input-wrap">
                <span class="input-prefix">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="grossIncome" name="grossIncome" min="0" step="any" value="<%= form.grossIncome || '' %>" placeholder="75000" required>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="filingStatus">Filing Status</label>
              <select id="filingStatus" name="filingStatus">
                <option value="single" <%= (!form.filingStatus || form.filingStatus === 'single') ? 'selected' : '' %>>Single</option>
                <option value="marriedJoint" <%= form.filingStatus === 'marriedJoint' ? 'selected' : '' %>>Married Filing Jointly</option>
                <option value="marriedSeparate" <%= form.filingStatus === 'marriedSeparate' ? 'selected' : '' %>>Married Filing Separately</option>
                <option value="headHousehold" <%= form.filingStatus === 'headHousehold' ? 'selected' : '' %>>Head of Household</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="deductionType">Deduction Type</label>
              <select id="deductionType" name="deductionType">
                <option value="standard" <%= (!form.deductionType || form.deductionType === 'standard') ? 'selected' : '' %>>Standard Deduction</option>
                <option value="itemized" <%= form.deductionType === 'itemized' ? 'selected' : '' %>>Itemized Deduction</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="itemizedDeduction">Itemized Deduction Amount</label>
              <div class="input-wrap">
                <span class="input-prefix">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="itemizedDeduction" name="itemizedDeduction" min="0" step="any" value="<%= form.itemizedDeduction || '' %>" placeholder="0">
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="federalWithheld">Federal Tax Withheld</label>
              <div class="input-wrap">
                <span class="input-prefix">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="federalWithheld" name="federalWithheld" min="0" step="any" value="<%= form.federalWithheld || '' %>" placeholder="0">
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="taxCredits">Tax Credits</label>
              <div class="input-wrap">
                <span class="input-prefix">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="taxCredits" name="taxCredits" min="0" step="any" value="<%= form.taxCredits || '' %>" placeholder="0">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="form-actions">
            <button type="submit" class="btn-calc">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M7 8h4M7 12h8"/></svg>
              Calculate Tax Estimate
            </button>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>

      <div class="ad-zone">
        <div class="ad-zone-label">Advertisement</div>
        <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-5193834725888549" data-ad-slot="5205436277" data-ad-format="auto" data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
        <script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div class="state-faq-section">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions — <%= state.name %> Income Tax</h2>
        <% if (state.hasIncomeTax) { %>
        <div class="state-faq-item">
          <h3>Does <%= state.name %> have a state income tax?</h3>
          <p>Yes. <%= state.name %> imposes a state income tax with a <%= state.topRate === state.bottomRate ? 'flat rate of ' + state.topRate + '%' : 'top marginal rate of ' + state.topRate + '%' %>. This is separate from your federal income tax obligation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="state-faq-item">
          <h3>What is the <%= state.name %> income tax rate for 2025?</h3>
          <p><% if (state.topRate === state.bottomRate) { %><%= state.name %> uses a flat income tax rate of <%= state.topRate %>% on all taxable income, regardless of income level or filing status.<% } else { %><%= state.name %> uses a graduated income tax system with rates from <%= state.bottomRate %>% to <%= state.topRate %>%. Only the income within each bracket is taxed at that bracket's rate — not your entire income.<% } %></p>
        </div>
        <div class="state-faq-item">
          <h3>Do I have to file a <%= state.name %> state tax return?</h3>
          <p>Most full-year <%= state.name %> residents with income above the state filing threshold must file a state return. Check the <a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a> for current thresholds and requirements.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="state-faq-item">
          <h3>How accurate is this <%= state.name %> state tax estimate?</h3>
          <p>This is a planning estimate. The state result uses <%= state.name %>'s published brackets but does not account for all state deductions, credits, exemptions, or local taxes. Verify with official <%= state.name %> tax forms or a qualified tax professional.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="state-faq-item">
          <h3>Does this calculator include federal income tax?</h3>
          <p>Yes. The results show your estimated <%= state.name %> state income tax and your federal income tax using 2025 federal brackets — your full combined picture in one place.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="state-faq-item">
          <h3>Where can I find official <%= state.name %> tax forms?</h3>
          <p>Official forms, instructions, and filing guidance are available at the <a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a>.</p>
        </div>
        <% } else { %>
        <div class="state-faq-item">
          <h3>Does <%= state.name %> have a state income tax?</h3>
          <p>No. <%= state.name %> does not impose a broad-based state income tax on wages, salaries, or most personal income. <%= state.noTaxNote %></p>
        </div>
        <div class="state-faq-item">
          <h3>Do I still owe federal income tax as a <%= state.name %> resident?</h3>
          <p>Yes. Federal income tax applies to all U.S. residents regardless of state. <%= state.name %> residents pay the same federal tax brackets as everyone else — only your state income tax is $0.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="state-faq-item">
          <h3>What taxes do <%= state.name %> residents pay instead of income tax?</h3>
          <p><%= state.overview.substring(0, 350) %>...</p>
        </div>
        <div class="state-faq-item">
          <h3>Do I need to file a <%= state.name %> state tax return?</h3>
          <p><%= state.name %> does not require a personal income tax return for most residents. You must still file a federal return with the IRS. Check the <a href="<%= state.revenueUrl.url %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><%= state.revenueUrl.label %></a> for any state-specific obligations that may apply.</p>
        </div>
        <% } %>
      </div>

